      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While dehydration can sometimes worsen lithium side effects, drinking additional water is not a guaranteed cure for nausea or tremors and can actually lead to dangerous lithium toxicity if it dilutes the medication levels in your blood. Because lithium interacts closely with kidney function and hydration status, self-managing these symptoms without blood work makes it impossible to know if your levels are safe or if you need immediate medical attention. Given the serious risks of lithium toxicity, which can be life-threatening even with stable blood thinning, please speak with your doctor or pharmacist regarding the cost concerns so you can address them safely.",
